 From occupational therapy records, investigators obtained self-report data of the ADLRS-3.

 Confirmatory factor analysis (CFA) was conducted to examine the 10 one-factor structures.

 If a domain showed an insufficient model fit, exploratory factor analysis (EFA) was performed to investigate the factor structure and choose one factor representing the original construct.

 Internal consistency was examined using Cronbach's alpha.

 Ceiling and floor effects were determined by the percentage of participants with the maximum and minimum scores in each domain, respectively.

